item.title: Home
item.description: About I am a computer science PhD Candidate at Stanford University working on parallel and distributed systems, currently rotating with Alex Aiken. Before that, I was a software engineer at Cockroach Labs working on CockroachDB. I am fortunate to be supported by an NSF Graduate Research Fellowship. Outside of work, you can find me lifting weights, playing tennis, and over eating. My resume is available here. Research I’m broadly interested in algorithms, computer systems, and programming languages.
